text: Aerial parts and seeds of Foeniculum vulgare Mill . oils possess different chemical compositions , nevertheless in what concerns the antioxidant activity , the authors in [ 57 ] found that for higher concentrations of essential oils ( > 750 mg / L for the aerial parts and > 1 , 000 mg / L for seeds ) a decrease of the activity was observed , suggesting that high concentrations of essential oils possess a pro - oxidant activity , independent of their richness in trans - anethole ( aerial parts ) or methyl chavicol ( seeds ) .
